* :TtbOaXl5v76Elo4Q: a design pattern used to offer some functionality to a group of classes without defining that functionality in each of them. A Servant is a class whose instance (or even just class) provides methods that take care of a desired service, while objects for which (or with whom) the servant does something, are taken as parameters
    @created 1380998042525
    @weight 0.5
